# report-generation-system

Core Report Generation Components:

1. Daily Progress Notes (DPN)
Importance Score: 90
- AI-enhanced narrative generation system for daily behavioral observations
- Auto-calculation of rating metrics across peer/adult interactions and investment levels 
- Period-specific data aggregation for weekly/biweekly/monthly summaries
- Clinical formatting rules enforcement

2. Service Plan Reports
Importance Score: 85
- 60-day compliance cycle tracking with automated scheduling
- AI-assisted content generation using historical case notes
- Multi-source data aggregation (behavior points, ratings, school scores)
- Professional clinical documentation standards enforcement
- Auto-population from behavioral metrics and assessment data

3. Progress Evaluation Reports
Importance Score: 80
- Rating normalization between 0-4 and 0-5 scale systems
- Multi-source scoring aggregation (daily ratings, weekly evaluations)
- Clinical assessment formatting with specialized sections
- Treatment goal progress tracking with 5-level measurement scale

4. Court Documentation System
Importance Score: 75
- Specialized legal documentation formatting
- Integration of behavioral metrics and incident reports
- Risk assessment inclusion with HYRNA scoring
- Treatment compliance documentation
- Discharge timeline projections

Key Report Generation Features:
- AI-enhanced narrative generation
- Clinical documentation standards
- Multi-source data aggregation
- Compliance period tracking
- Professional formatting rules
- Treatment goal progression
- Legal documentation requirements

Business Rules:
- Reports must follow clinical documentation standards
- AI narratives require staff review/approval
- 60-day service plan update requirements
- Court documentation must include risk assessments
- Progress evaluations require multiple data sources

